12 It is as true as terrible, iudgement may be prolonged, but when the mouth of the Lord hath ſpoken, by no power it can be avoided. The ſixt day enſued, which as if it had had a divine diſpenſation to breake the ſixt cō
                  mandement, ſlew our PRINCE. A day, that hath beene Principibus infeſta & infauſta; witneſſe the death of Richard the firſt, the ſixt of Aprill;1199 Henry the ſecond, the 6 of Iuly;
               1189
               Edward the firſt, the 6 of Iuly;
               1307 & our laſt Edward, bleſſed K. Edward the 6. on the 6 of Iuly;
               1553 as alſo this 6 day of November, wherein our, Iulium ſydus, Prince HENRYES ſunne did ſet.
